article.headline: Toledo 103, Wright St 66
article.story: TOLEDO, Ohio (AP) -- Keith Triplett had 21 points and Sammy Villegas added 18 to lead Toledo to a 103-66 victory over Wright State on Monday. The Rockets (7-1) shot 63 percent from 3-point range, making 17 of 27 attempts, including 5-for-7 by Villegas and 5-of-8 for Triplett. The Raiders made just two of 10 3-pointers, including five misses by Seth Doliboa. Vernard Hollins scored 14 points to lead Wright State (2-6), while Vova Severovas scored 12 and Doliboa and Drew Burleson each added 10 points. The Rockets' depth outdid Wright State; nine players scored off the Toledo bench, while just four of five Raiders reserves scored. Toledo shot 58 percent (36-of-62) on field goals to 43 percent (23-of-53) for the Raiders.
